{"id": "EUVD-2022-54485", "enisaUuid": "e9d0810e-224b-3244-ad61-6408b6a6717b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nref_tracker: implement use-after-free detection\n\nWhenever ref_tracker_dir_init() is called, mark the struct ref_tracker_dir\nas dead.\n\nTest the dead status from ref_tracker_alloc() and ref_tracker_free()\n\nThis should detect buggy dev_put()/dev_hold() happening too late\nin netdevice dismantle process.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T21:32:12", "dateUpdated": "2025-02-27T21:32:12", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3743c9de303fa36c2e2ca2522ab280c52bcafbd2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e3ececfe668facd87d920b608349a32607060e66", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49127"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49127"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00b368ae-0976-3c4f-9bfc-9b72539580f4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4e66934eaadc83b27ada8d42b60894018f3bfabf <e3ececfe668facd87d920b608349a32607060e66"}, {"id": "1a8ead75-2ccf-3113-9176-c3db0f989dc6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "21cb00a6-a814-3a39-9025-58322bcaba41", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4e66934eaadc83b27ada8d42b60894018f3bfabf <3743c9de303fa36c2e2ca2522ab280c52bcafbd2"}, {"id": "484dcb79-8de3-3279-83ef-836ad8063e1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "85add595-e222-3690-bcfc-a6337eaa0da1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.3"}, {"id": "d752ee44-8e2a-352d-8384-dd195848b7a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "dc9ea6e8-fa2e-3b8d-9b29-cf5eaba7aecf", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}